<subSubSection id="C329E097090F465BFF08CA01FBBF213D" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" type="type_taxon">
<paragraph id="8B8CB31C090F465BFF08CA01FDAB2730" blockId="5.[151,588,822,845]" box="[151,588,822,845]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<emphasis id="B9476F0E090F465BFF08CA01FEC52731" bold="true" box="[151,290,822,845]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<typeStatus id="54880DBE090F465BFF08CA01FF2B2730" box="[151,204,823,844]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Type</typeStatus>
species.
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C33C89F090F465BFEB6CA01FE122731" authority="Nielson, 2011" authorityName="Nielson" authorityYear="2011" box="[297,501,823,845]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Freytagolidia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ligula" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B9476F0E090F465BFEB6CA01FE122731" box="[297,501,823,845]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Freytagolidia ligula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B9476F0E090F465BFE64CA01FDAB2730" bold="true" box="[507,588,823,844]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A274D275090F465BFE64CA01FDAB2730" box="[507,588,823,844]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8CB31C090F465BFF08CA4FFC242039" blockId="5.[151,1436,889,1597]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<emphasis id="B9476F0E090F465BFF08CA4FFE7927ED" bold="true" box="[151,414,889,913]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" reason="1">External morphology.</emphasis>
General color dark, golden brown to black with yellow transverse band on pronotum and crown. Head narrower than pronotum, anterior margin obtusely angulate; crown broad, equal to width of eyes, produced distally beyond anterior margin of eyes for about 1/3 of entire median length; eyes semiglobular; pronotum shorter than median length of crown; mesonotum large, twice as long as median length of pronotum; forewings long, broad; clypeus long, narrow, median longitudinal carina prominent; clypellus short, less than 1/3 as long as clypeus, narrow basally, inflated medio-basally, apex expanded laterally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8CB31C090F465BFF5ACD67FBBF213D" blockId="5.[151,1436,889,1597]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<emphasis id="B9476F0E090F465BFF5ACD67FE912016" bold="true" box="[197,374,1105,1130]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" reason="1">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Pygofer in lateral view broad, with prominent, setaceous caudodorsal lobe projecting ventrally, long, robust caudoventral process reaching to lobe (
<figureCitation id="1308AF99090F465BFD6ECD43FCC920F1" box="[753,814,1141,1165]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–8" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1897,1920]" captionTargetBox="[182,1405,230,1853]" captionTargetId="figure-72@7.[151,1436,193,1876]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 1–8. Freytagolidia ligula sp. nov. (1) pygofer and segment X, lateral view; (2) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (3) right style, dorsal view; (4) right style, lateral view; (5) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (6) aedeagus and dorsal connective, ventral view; (7) connective, dorsal view; (8) dorsal connective, dorsal view." pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Fig.1</figureCitation>
); subgenital plate in ventral view very long, broad in basal half, ligulate in distal half, setaceous (
<figureCitation id="1308AF99090F465BFD16CDAFFD2820CD" box="[649,719,1177,1201]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–8" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1897,1920]" captionTargetBox="[182,1405,230,1853]" captionTargetId="figure-72@7.[151,1436,193,1876]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 1–8. Freytagolidia ligula sp. nov. (1) pygofer and segment X, lateral view; (2) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (3) right style, dorsal view; (4) right style, lateral view; (5) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (6) aedeagus and dorsal connective, ventral view; (7) connective, dorsal view; (8) dorsal connective, dorsal view." pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
); connective broadly Y-shaped, stem short, membranous medially (
<figureCitation id="1308AF99090F465BFF4FCD8BFEF320A9" box="[208,276,1213,1237]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–8" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1897,1920]" captionTargetBox="[182,1405,230,1853]" captionTargetId="figure-72@7.[151,1436,193,1876]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 1–8. Freytagolidia ligula sp. nov. (1) pygofer and segment X, lateral view; (2) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (3) right style, dorsal view; (4) right style, lateral view; (5) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (6) aedeagus and dorsal connective, ventral view; (7) connective, dorsal view; (8) dorsal connective, dorsal view." pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
); style short, not as long as aedeagus, apophysis narrow, attenuated distally (
<figureCitation id="1308AF99090F465BFBF1CD8BFB3D20A9" box="[1134,1242,1213,1237]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–8" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1897,1920]" captionTargetBox="[182,1405,230,1853]" captionTargetId="figure-72@7.[151,1436,193,1876]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 1–8. Freytagolidia ligula sp. nov. (1) pygofer and segment X, lateral view; (2) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (3) right style, dorsal view; (4) right style, lateral view; (5) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (6) aedeagus and dorsal connective, ventral view; (7) connective, dorsal view; (8) dorsal connective, dorsal view." pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Figs. 3, 4</figureCitation>
); aedeagus short, tubular, shaft setaceous, gonopore sub-basal and exiting laterally in ventral view (
<figureCitation id="1308AF99090F465BFBB3CDD7FB972085" box="[1068,1136,1249,1273]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–8" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1897,1920]" captionTargetBox="[182,1405,230,1853]" captionTargetId="figure-72@7.[151,1436,193,1876]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 1–8. Freytagolidia ligula sp. nov. (1) pygofer and segment X, lateral view; (2) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (3) right style, dorsal view; (4) right style, lateral view; (5) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (6) aedeagus and dorsal connective, ventral view; (7) connective, dorsal view; (8) dorsal connective, dorsal view." pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
) and curved laterally, with attached dorsal connective lying ventrally in lateral view (
<figureCitation id="1308AF99090F465BFC80CC33FC842161" box="[799,867,1285,1309]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–8" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1897,1920]" captionTargetBox="[182,1405,230,1853]" captionTargetId="figure-72@7.[151,1436,193,1876]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 1–8. Freytagolidia ligula sp. nov. (1) pygofer and segment X, lateral view; (2) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (3) right style, dorsal view; (4) right style, lateral view; (5) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (6) aedeagus and dorsal connective, ventral view; (7) connective, dorsal view; (8) dorsal connective, dorsal view." pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
); dorsal connective (
<figureCitation id="1308AF99090F465BFBD2CC33FB362161" box="[1101,1233,1285,1309]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–8" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1897,1920]" captionTargetBox="[182,1405,230,1853]" captionTargetId="figure-72@7.[151,1436,193,1876]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 1–8. Freytagolidia ligula sp. nov. (1) pygofer and segment X, lateral view; (2) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (3) right style, dorsal view; (4) right style, lateral view; (5) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (6) aedeagus and dorsal connective, ventral view; (7) connective, dorsal view; (8) dorsal connective, dorsal view." pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Figs. 5, 6, 8</figureCitation>
) nearly as long as aedeagus, bifurcate basally and with membranous flange on each side in ventral view.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C329E097090F465BFF5ACC7BFD9221F6" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8B8CB31C090F465BFF5ACC7BFD9221F6" blockId="5.[151,1436,889,1597]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<emphasis id="B9476F0E090F465BFF5ACC7BFEAC2119" bold="true" box="[197,331,1357,1381]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" reason="1">Etymology.</emphasis>
The generic name is a patronym, named for Dr. Paul H. Freytag who has a distinguished record of fine contributions in leafhopper taxonomy.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C329E097090F465BFF5ACCA3FE4C2241" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B8CB31C090F465BFF5ACCA3FE4C2241" blockId="5.[151,1436,889,1597]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<emphasis id="B9476F0E090F465BFF5ACCA3FEDE21D1" bold="true" box="[197,313,1429,1453]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" reason="1">Remarks.</emphasis>
The 
<typeStatus id="54880DBE090F465BFEE9CCA0FE4121D2" box="[374,422,1430,1454]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">type</typeStatus>
species is large and robust, similar in general habitus to 
<taxonomicName id="4C33C89F090F465BFBA6CCA0FA8D21D1" authority="Nielson, 1979" authorityName="Nielson" authorityYear="1979" box="[1081,1386,1429,1453]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Korsigianus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9476F0E090F465BFBA6CCA0FB2521D1" box="[1081,1218,1430,1453]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Korsigianus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFA2CEED090F465BFB54CCA3FA8D21D1" author="Nielson, M. W." box="[1227,1386,1429,1453]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="1 - 329" refId="ref33690" refString="Nielson, M. W. (1979 e) A revision of the subfamily Coelidiinae (Homptera: Cicadellidae). III. Tribe Teruliini. Pacific Insects - Monograph, 35 1 - 329." type="journal article" year="1979">Nielson, 1979</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C33C89F090F465BFF08CC8CFE4421AD" authority="Nielson. The" authorityName="Nielson. The" authorityYear="1979" box="[151,419,1465,1489]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Licontinia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9476F0E090F465BFF08CC8CFEED21AD" box="[151,266,1466,1489]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Licontinia</emphasis>
Nielson. The
</taxonomicName>
male genitalia are distinctive. The genus has a unique subgenital plate in which the distal half is a long, ligulate process (
<figureCitation id="1308AF99090F465BFE6BCCEBFDDE2189" box="[500,569,1501,1525]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–8" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1897,1920]" captionTargetBox="[182,1405,230,1853]" captionTargetId="figure-72@7.[151,1436,193,1876]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 1–8. Freytagolidia ligula sp. nov. (1) pygofer and segment X, lateral view; (2) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (3) right style, dorsal view; (4) right style, lateral view; (5) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (6) aedeagus and dorsal connective, ventral view; (7) connective, dorsal view; (8) dorsal connective, dorsal view." pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
). The flanged dorsal connective is also distinctive (
<figureCitation id="1308AF99090F465BFBE6CCEBFB032189" box="[1145,1252,1501,1525]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–8" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1897,1920]" captionTargetBox="[182,1405,230,1853]" captionTargetId="figure-72@7.[151,1436,193,1876]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 1–8. Freytagolidia ligula sp. nov. (1) pygofer and segment X, lateral view; (2) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (3) right style, dorsal view; (4) right style, lateral view; (5) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (6) aedeagus and dorsal connective, ventral view; (7) connective, dorsal view; (8) dorsal connective, dorsal view." pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Figs. 5, 8</figureCitation>
). These features will separate 
<taxonomicName id="4C33C89F090F465BFEB1CF37FE202265" authorityName="Nielson" authorityYear="2011" box="[302,455,1537,1561]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Freytagolidia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9476F0E090F465BFEB1CF37FE202265" box="[302,455,1537,1561]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Freytagolidia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from all other known genera in the tribe. The genus is monobasic, known only from 1 species presented below.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
